<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>Resin Polishing on eQualle Blog</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/categories/resin-polishing/</link><description>Recent posts on eQualle Blog</description><generator>Hugo 0.150.1</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://blog.equalle.com/categories/resin-polishing/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Avoid Contamination From Silicone</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 23 Mar 2026 14:21:05 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><category>grit-600</category><category>grit-800</category><category>grit-1500</category><category>dust control</category><category>polishing pads</category><description>Stop fish eyes and cure issues. Learn silicone-safe prep, sanding, and resin polishing workflows for clear epoxy and reliable silicone casting.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-without-silicone-contamination"&gt;Resin polishing without silicone contamination&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s a quiet joy to the last ten minutes of a build. The tools are put away. The dust has settled. You pull a cured coaster from its mold, or lift a small river table into the light, and the surface flashes back — a depth that feels almost impossible. You reach for your compounds, line up the pads, and begin resin polishing, already picturing that glass-smooth finish. Then, just as the sheen appears, a few round craters show up. The polish drags around them like water around a pebble. A couple more passes and they don’t go away. If anything, they multiply. The feeling in your stomach drops: fisheyes.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/24.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/23/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-contamination-from-silicone-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>10</readingTime></item><item><title>Fix Haze By Stepping Back To 3000</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 14:41:14 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-800</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit-2000</category><category>grit-3000</category><description>Learn how to fix sanding haze fast with a pro resin polishing workflow—step back to 3000 grit, control heat, and finish to a deep, glassy gloss.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000"&gt;Resin Polishing: Fix Haze by Stepping Back to 3000&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It always starts the same way. You pour a clear epoxy for a keepsake, a river board, or a crisp acrylic panel that needs to look like still water. You sand it flat, chase out a couple of dust pimples, then bring in the buffer. Instead of that mirror you pictured, you’re left with a milky haze that looks dull unless it’s wet. If you’re here, you’ve probably tried a hotter pad or a more aggressive compound and only made the bloom worse. I’ve been there—late at night in the shop, lights angled low, hand sliding across the piece, feeling a finish that’s glass-smooth yet visually cloudy. That’s the kind of moment that separates guessing from knowing. The difference is a repeatable workflow and one simple fix that saves the day more often than not: stepping back to 3000.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/08.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/03/03/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/fix-haze-by-stepping-back-to-3000-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Protective Coats After Resin Polish</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 13 Feb 2026 15:26:33 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-800</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit-2000</category><category>clear coat</category><description>Engineer-tested guide to protective coats after resin polishing—what to use, how to prep, and how each topcoat performs for gloss, durability, and UV</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="protective-coats-after-resin-polishing-what-works"&gt;Protective Coats After Resin Polishing: What Works&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the dust finally settles in the workshop, there’s a moment you can feel in your chest. The lathe is quiet, the last microfiber swipe lifts away the white slurry, and the piece in your hands—whether it’s an epoxy river table or a turned resin pen—throws back a clean, high-contrast reflection. It’s the payoff of patient sanding, controlled heat, and precise resin polishing. That mirror isn’t an accident. It’s the product of abrasive selection, pressure control, and respecting the thermal limits of thermoset polymers. And yet, if you’ve been here before, you also know what can happen in a week: faint holograms that show up under raking light, microscratches from a soft cloth, maybe a dull watermark from a coffee mug.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/21.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/13/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/protective-coats-after-resin-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Panel Wipe To Remove Polishing Oils</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 26 Jan 2026 16:23:07 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-2000</category><category>grit-3000</category><category>clear coat</category><description>Learn the science and workflow of panel wipe to remove polishing oils, reveal true finish, and prep surfaces for coatings during resin polishing.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="panel-wipe-for-flawless-resin-polishing-results"&gt;Panel Wipe for Flawless Resin Polishing Results&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saturday, 4 p.m., the garage is cooler than it’s been all day. You’ve completed the final compounding pass, refined with a finishing polish, and the panels look slick under diffuse light. The gloss reads high, the reflections are crisp, and for a moment you’re tempted to call it. But you know better. Finishing oils are doing what they’re designed to do—lubricate abrasives, enhance wipe-off, and temporarily mask micro-marring. If you skip a proper panel wipe at this point, you don’t really know what you’re sealing in. Whether you’re prepping a urethane clear coat, a cured epoxy countertop, or a cast acrylic lens, the truth of resin polishing only appears after the oils are gone.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/05.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/26/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/panel-wipe-to-remove-polishing-oils-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Check Clarity Under Strong Lighting</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 05 Jan 2026 15:59:00 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-600</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit-2000</category><category>grit-3000</category><category>wet sanding</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Master resin polishing and clarity checks under strong lighting with practical steps, inspection setups, and troubleshooting for crystal-clear finishes.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-how-to-check-clarity-under-light"&gt;Resin Polishing: How to Check Clarity Under Light&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The moment you flip on a bright desk lamp is when the truth comes out. A pendant you poured, sanded, and buffed over a quiet weekend looks flawless under normal room light. But under that focused beam, faint fog appears along the edges. Micro-swirls show up in arcs you didn’t notice before. A tiny speck you thought you removed winks back at you. If you’ve tried resin polishing even a few times, you’ve seen this: strong light is uncompromising. It magnifies every scratch, ripple, and residue, turning a “good” finish into one you’re not quite ready to sign your name to.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/18.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/05/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/check-clarity-under-strong-lighting-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Clean Pads To Prevent Micro Marring</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2025 16:21:55 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>clear coat</category><category>polishing pads</category><description>Stop swirls and haze. Learn a pro workflow for clean pads, resin polishing, and flawless finishes without micro marring on paint, epoxy, and acrylic.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-clean-pads-zero-micro-marring"&gt;Resin Polishing: Clean Pads, Zero Micro Marring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’ve watched the same scene a hundred times: you finish a long day of shaping, sanding, and dialing in the gloss. The shop is quiet, the floor swept, your coffee cold. You swing the work light across the panel—maybe it’s a black hood, a river table, or a batch of resin bangles—and your stomach sinks. There it is: a faint gray haze of tiny trails that weren’t visible under the shop lights. That’s micro marring, and nine times out of ten it’s not your machine, polish, or even your technique—it’s what’s happening at the pad face. This is where cleaning while you work becomes the difference between “almost” and “absolutely flawless,” whether you’re finishing paint or doing resin polishing on jewelry and tabletops.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/02.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/17/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/clean-pads-to-prevent-micro-marring-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>10</readingTime></item><item><title>Avoid Overheating Edges During Polish</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 01 Dec 2025 16:10:07 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-2000</category><category>wet sanding</category><description>Engineer-tested methods to keep resin edges cool while polishing. Learn speeds, abrasives, and wet-sanding techniques that prevent melt, haze, and cracks.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-without-overheating-edges"&gt;Resin Polishing Without Overheating Edges&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first time I overheated a resin edge, it looked perfect—right up until it wasn’t. The surface was glossy, but the perimeter turned milky, then smeared like warm butter under a rotary pad. I could smell the polymer heating. It felt like a setback on a simple task: sanding and finishing a handmade resin coaster. If you’ve been there, you know the mix of frustration and “what did I do wrong?” It’s not lack of care; it’s physics. That edge has less mass to absorb heat, and during resin polishing you’re pushing friction and pressure into a tiny contact patch. Heat has nowhere to go.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/15.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/01/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/avoid-overheating-edges-during-polish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>10</readingTime></item><item><title>Choose Pad And Compound For Plastics</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 18 Nov 2025 13:37:22 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-600</category><category>grit-800</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit-1500</category><category>grit-2000</category><category>grit-3000</category><category>grit progression</category><category>sanding block</category><category>polishing pads</category><description>Engineer’s guide to resin polishing: pick the right pad and compound for acrylic, polycarbonate, and epoxy. Tested combos, heat control, and pro tips.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-pads-and-compounds-for-plastics"&gt;Resin polishing: Pads and compounds for plastics&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On a quiet Saturday, I watched a friend slowly lower a buffing pad onto the cloudy edge of his epoxy river table. The coffee mugs had left fine scuffs; sunlight turned them into halos. He’d already tried an all-purpose metal polish and a “universal” wool pad—both grabbed hard, smeared the surface, and left the epoxy warmer than I liked. He looked at me and asked the question I hear weekly: “Which pad and which compound do I actually use for plastics?” It’s an honest question with costly consequences if you guess wrong. Unlike metal paint systems that tolerate a surprising amount of heat and pressure, plastics and cured resins can haze, smear, or stress-craze from a few seconds of the wrong contact.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/01.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/18/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/choose-pad-and-compound-for-plastics-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>13</readingTime></item><item><title>Remove 1500–2000 Grit Marks On Resin</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 07 Nov 2025 23:56:25 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit-1200</category><category>grit-1500</category><category>grit-2000</category><category>grit-2500</category><category>grit-3000</category><category>dust control</category><description>Expert workflows to remove 1500–2000 grit marks on resin and achieve optical clarity with the right abrasives, compounds, and heat control.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-erasing-15002000-grit-scratches"&gt;Resin Polishing: Erasing 1500–2000 Grit Scratches&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pendant looked flawless on the bench last night—glassy, color suspended in amber, edges softened just so. Then morning light hit it. Under a low-angle window beam, micro-scratches flared across the surface like frost on a windshield. You could feel your shoulders sag. You did the careful wet-sand through 1500 and 2000, kept the strokes even, swirled the slurry away. It should be done. But resin is unforgiving under raking light, and 1500–2000 grit marks hang on, whisper-thin but brutally visible. This is the moment where the craft turns from “sanding” to resin polishing: closing the cut, controlling heat, and stepping the abrasive system with intent until the surface stops being a surface and becomes a reflection.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/07/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/remove-1500-2000-grit-marks-on-resin-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>9</readingTime></item><item><title>Polish Epoxy Resin To Glass Like Finish</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 03 Nov 2025 21:00:08 +0000</pubDate><category>Resin Polishing</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><category>grit-600</category><category>grit-800</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit-1500</category><description>Learn how to polish epoxy resin to a glass-like finish with step-by-step sanding, heat control, compounds, and pro tips for durable clarity.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="resin-polishing-for-a-glass-like-epoxy-finish"&gt;Resin Polishing for a Glass-Like Epoxy Finish&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first time you run a fingertip across an epoxy surface, it’s a little magic trick. The light catches, colors bloom, and you expect the kind of clarity you see on showroom glass. But if you’ve poured, leveled, and cured resin yourself, you also know the moment that follows: under sunlight or a raking lamp, faint haze, scratch patterns, or tiny undulations whisper that the job isn’t quite done. That’s where resonant craftsmanship meets patience—where resin polishing turns a good pour into a gleaming, glass-like finish.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/instagram/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/pinterest/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing/cards/facebook/polish-epoxy-resin-to-glass-like-finish-resin-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>14</readingTime></item></channel></rss>